For example, the `while` in the [first sample question](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sample_question#Input) is:

\begin{code}
While (condition) { statements ; }
\end{code}(where the condition should be `true` for all values of `variable_name`, which is equal to `number_of_puppies` in "three times five less than", and `number_of_Dobermans` in "how many Schnauzels" and "how many seashells". This makes it a while loop, that asks a question, then does more things based on the answer you gave it).

In the [second sample question](http://www.enotes.com/homework-help/doctor-banks-330-toothbrushes-give-away-patients-537561), the `condition` is `number_of_past_day!= number_of_future_day`, which is `true` for `number_of_future day > number_of_past day`. So, the while loop here is,

\begin{pre}

while (number_of_futur_day > number_of_pret_day)
  statements ;
}

